<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1806,2033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="396">
1 Pronotum slightly transverse, with irregular lateral crenulation. Elytra short, slightly longer than pronotum; wings reduced to short stubs. Forebody reddish-brown. Aedeagus as in Fig. 10 (
<bibRefCitation author="Shavrin, A. V. &amp; Mullen, L." box="[826,1061,1835,1857]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" pagination="121 - 128" refId="ref3792" refString="Shavrin, A. V. &amp; Mullen, L. (2015) Phlaeopterus Motschulsky, 1853 (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Omaliinae: Anthophagini) - a new genus for the Palaearctic: new combination. Zootaxa, 4028 (1), 121 - 128. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4028.1.5" type="journal article" year="2015">Shavrin &amp; Mullen 2015</bibRefCitation>
). Body length: 4.00– 
<quantity box="[1263,1352,1835,1856]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" unit="mm" value="4.3">4.30 mm</quantity>
. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[277,333,1864,1886]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1944,1969]" captionTargetBox="[191,1398,189,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[178,1410,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Phlaeopterus hromadkai: 1—habitus, 2—labrum (dorsal view), 3—left and right mandibles (dorsal view), 4—labium (dorsal view), 5—mentum (dorsal view), 6—left maxilla (dorsal view), 7—aedeagus (parameral view), 8—aedeagus (lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3609635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3609635/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Shavrin, A. V. &amp; Mullen, L." box="[345,579,1864,1886]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" pagination="121 - 128" refId="ref3792" refString="Shavrin, A. V. &amp; Mullen, L. (2015) Phlaeopterus Motschulsky, 1853 (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Omaliinae: Anthophagini) - a new genus for the Palaearctic: new combination. Zootaxa, 4028 (1), 121 - 128. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4028.1.5" type="journal article" year="2015">Shavrin &amp; Mullen 2015</bibRefCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[595,663,1864,1886]" name="Russia" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Russia</collectingCountry>
: Eastern Siberia …....................................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shavrin &amp; Mullen" authorityYear="2015" box="[1332,1436,1864,1886]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Phlaeopterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="czerskyi">
<emphasis box="[1332,1347,1865,1886]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1359,1436,1864,1885]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">czerskyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1806,2033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="396">
- Pronotum distinctly transverse, with regular lateral crenulation. Elytra long, about twice as long as pronotum; wings fully developed. 
<collectingCountry box="[314,371,1923,1945]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">China</collectingCountry>
….................................................................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="397" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1806,2033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="396">
2 Lateral portions of pronotum with moderately small pits. Forebody reddish-brown to brown, sometimes with very indistinct spots on elytra. Aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation box="[528,586,1982,2004]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1944,1969]" captionTargetBox="[191,1398,189,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[178,1410,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Phlaeopterus hromadkai: 1—habitus, 2—labrum (dorsal view), 3—left and right mandibles (dorsal view), 4—labium (dorsal view), 5—mentum (dorsal view), 6—left maxilla (dorsal view), 7—aedeagus (parameral view), 8—aedeagus (lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3609635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3609635/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
. Body length: 
<quantity box="[726,868,1981,2003]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.975" metricValueMax="4.2" metricValueMin="3.75" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" unit="mm" value="3.975" valueMax="4.2" valueMin="3.75">3.75–4.20 mm</quantity>
. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[1009,1066,1982,2004]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1944,1969]" captionTargetBox="[191,1398,189,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[178,1410,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Phlaeopterus hromadkai: 1—habitus, 2—labrum (dorsal view), 3—left and right mandibles (dorsal view), 4—labium (dorsal view), 5—mentum (dorsal view), 6—left maxilla (dorsal view), 7—aedeagus (parameral view), 8—aedeagus (lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3609635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3609635/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
. 
<collectingRegion box="[1077,1138,1982,2003]" country="China" name="Gansu" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">Gansu</collectingRegion>
…................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Shavrin" authorityName="Shavrin" authorityYear="2020" box="[1166,1379,2011,2033]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Phlaeopterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hromadkai" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis box="[1166,1181,2012,2033]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="396">P</emphasis>
